[1] Cholera - Malawi (Southern region)
Date: Mon 21 Aug 2017
Source: Capital Radio Malawi [summ., edited]
https://www.capitalradiomalawi.com/index.php/blog/local-news/local-news/item/8352-chikwawa-hit-by-cholera-outbreak


A total of 9 people are admitted to Chikwawa district [Southern region] hospital following a cholera outbreak. This comes barely 4 months after another outbreak hit the district's 2 villages in the area of Paramount Chief Lundu, affecting 38 people. The Environmental Health Office for Chikwawa district has confirmed the development, citing poor access to safe water and poor quality of sanitary facilities in villages. There are fears that the cholera outbreak may spread to other areas where communities do not have access to portable water supply as well as toilets.

