[3] Cholera - Sudan
Date: Fri 18 Aug 2017
Source: Radio Dabanga [edited]
https://www.dabangasudan.org/en/all-news/article/fifteen-cholera-dead-in-west-darfur-camp


West Darfur
-----------
15 people have died of cholera while 18 others have been infected in Murnei, West Darfur, in the past 3 days. A sheikh in Murnei camp for displaced people told this station, "18 people are now in the isolation ward in the camp." The 18 infected people came from Um Tajok village near Murnei on [9 Aug 2017]. 6 people died of cholera at the village that day, a sheikh reported from the camp last week [week of 7 Aug 2017].

Blue Nile
---------
In Blue Nile state, 3 brothers died in the hospital of Ed Damazin on [Tue 15 Aug 2017]. A relative of the deceased told Radio Dabanga that the 3 family members died of the same disease in the hospital, in El Hijra district.

Sennar
------
Meanwhile in Sennar, 18 people contracted cholera in El Dindir locality this week [week of 14 Aug 2017]. A medical source told this station that on [Thu 17 Aug 2017], El Dindir's hospital received 13 new cases of cholera, 8 of which were received earlier this week. 5 others arrived on [Thu 17 Aug 2017]. The medical isolation centre at Bardana village, south of the city, also recorded 5 new cases of cholera.

The hospital in Singa received 3 new cases of cholera on [Thu 17 Aug 2017]. A medical source informed Radio Dabanga that the 3 patients had come from Um Benin village, south east of Singa. "16 people suffering from cholera are still in the isolation ward."

Northern state
--------------
The 1st cases of cholera have been reported in the southern part of El Mahas in Northern state, at Arduan health centre. The patients arrived from Maljab area on [Thu 17 Aug 2017], while El Tura health centre of El Mahas received another case.

Nubian activist Adham Nasr told Radio Dabanga that the woman has been isolated in a room at Arduan health centre to receive treatment. There are concerns that the disease might break out in the area during the rainy season, which makes it difficult to move from and to Arduan.

Red Sea
-------
A health centre in Arayab area in Ganab, Red Sea state, received 5 children suffering from cholera on Wed 16 Aug 2017. Journalist Osman Hashim told Radio Dabanga that the one of them has been transferred to Port Sudan Hospital. The doctors were unable to give information about the cases. The hospital's administration has not allocated a ward to isolate the cholera patients.

Earlier in August 2017 a volunteer of one of the cholera awareness raising campaigns in Sudan told Radio Dabanga that the reality in the hospitals is very poor.

--
