[5] Cholera - India (Punjab)
Date: Sat 19 Aug 2017 03:09 PM IST
Source: Times of India [edited]
http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/ludhiana/cholera-outbreak-18-fresh-cases-reported-on-day-5/articleshow/60126504.cms


18 fresh cholera cases were reported at Guru Har Rai Nagar [Ludhiana, Punjab] on on day 5 of the outbreak. District epidemiologist Ramesh Kumar said more than 500 people contracted the disease over the past few days. Health officials are taking all possible measures to stem the outbreak, including organizing medical camps to engender public awareness about the disease.

Meanwhile, sources said the health department is still trying to hide the exact number of cases reported in the camp. "No water samples have been collected on the 5th day of the outbreak. All the 18 patients have been admitted to private hospitals. Health officials are not paying attention to affected areas as a number of cases are being still being reported."

